<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.4.1/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-Vkoo8x4CGsO3+Hhxv8T/Q5PaXtkKtu6ug5TOeNV6gBiFeWPGFN9MuhOf23Q9Ifjh" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/index.css">
    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.4.1/jquery.min.js"></script>

    <script>
        $(document).ready(function() {

            $('#about').on('click', function() {
                $('html, body').animate({
                    scrollTop: $(".about").offset().top
                }, 2000);
            })

            $('#download').on('click', function() {
                $('html, body').animate({
                    scrollTop: $(".download").offset().top
                }, 2000);
            })

            $('#github').on('click', function() {
                $('html, body').animate({
                    scrollTop: $(".github").offset().top
                }, 2000);
            })

            $('.download-list').on('click', function() {
                $('.download-list li').toggleClass('active-download')
            })

        });
    </script>
    <title> CTF Challenges </title>
</head>
<body>

    <%- include('../partials/header.ejs') %>

    <div class="jumbotron" >
        <div class="container">
            <h1 class="display-4"> Portable CTF </h1>
            <p class="lead"> Challenges designed to be auto generated and work on the Raspberry Pi. </p>
            <hr class="my-4">
            <p> Build from github or download now below: </p>
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="https://github.com/Harry-Developer/Digital-Systems-Project" role="button">Build</a>
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="#" role="button">Download</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about">
        <div class="container">

            <h1> About Portable CTF </h1>
            <p>
                This project will be a portable CTF challenge, the aim is the produce a piece of software 
                that can generate a Pi image with a random challenge set. This image can then be loaded onto a 
                raspberry Pi, the aim for the user is to complete the CTF challenges to earn points. The challenges 
                will be set in groups, from web based to steganography.
            </p>

            <h2> Aims & Objectives </h2>
            <p class="lead"> The aims of this project is to produce a customisable portable CTF challenge. </p>


            <ul class="list-group-flush">
                <li class="list-group-item"> - Create a website to host customised Pi image generation. </li>
                <li class="list-group-item"> - Generate a custom Pi image.</li>
                <li class="list-group-item"> - Create CTF challenges with varying skill sets</li>
              </ul>

        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="download">
        
        <div class="container">
            <h1> Download </h1>
            <p class="lead"> Choose from the challenge options below to style your CTF. </p>

            <ul class="list-group list-group-horizontal-sm download-list">
                <li class="list-group-item active-download"> Web Based </li>
                <li class="list-group-item"> Miscellaneous </li>
            </ul> 
            <hr class="my-4">
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="#" role="button">Download</a>
        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="github">
        <div class="container">
            <h1> Github  </h1>
            <p class="lead"> Build yourself, or take a a look! </p>
            <hr class="my-4">
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="https://github.com/Harry-Developer/Digital-Systems-Project" role="button">Github</a>
        </div>

    </div>

    <%- include('../partials/footer.ejs') %>

</body>
</html>